This paper deals with online learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of adversarial models and the consideration of binary losses suggest that the paper may belong to the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The use of noisy feedback and the consideration of bandit feedback suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Information Theory" (cs.IT). The consideration of variable noise rates suggests that the paper may belong to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS), as this is a common topic in the analysis of algorithms. Finally, the use of regret bounds suggests that the paper may belong to the category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI), as regret analysis is often used in the study of online social networks.
